==English==
==Etymology==
Presumably derived from 'tropical' as the original meaning meant 'affected by war service in the tropics' (G.A.Wilkes, ''A Dictionary of Australian Colloquialisms'', Fontana, 1978).

===Adjective===
'''troppo'''

# {{AU}} {{slang}} [[crazy]], [[mad]], [[over the top]].
#:''Barry's gone '''troppo''' and married that [[sheila]] he's only known for two weeks.''

